==English==

===Etymology===
From Old English [[cēap]], ''[[trade]]''. Originally a loan from Latin [[caupō]], ''[[tradesman]]'', ''[[innkeeper]]'', whence also German [[kaufen]] ''[[buy]]'' and Finnish [[kauppa]], ''[[shop]]''.

